      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/116/5530",
      "text": [
        " اَلرَّجُلِ يَمُوتُ وَ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ فَيَضْمَنُهُ ضَامِنٌ لِلْغُرَمَاءِ قَالَ \"إِذَا رَضِيَ اَلْغُرَمَاءُ فَقَدْ بَرِئَتْ ذِمَّةُ اَلْمَيِّتِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5530 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan from Abu Abdullah (as), regarding a man who dies while owing a debt, and a guarantor assumes responsibility for it on behalf of the creditors.\nImam (as) said: \"If the creditors agree, then the deceased is cleared of responsibility.\""
        ]
      }
